SKILLS █

─────────────────────

Applied Claude Code skills — the ones that have survived several seasons of models
and audits. They still taste better than store-bought.

These are forged, probed, and pruned in the kitchen (github.com/claudialnathan/agent-kitchen):
HARVEST surfaces the gaps, FORGE turns them into artifacts, probes check they still
earn their place, HARNESS-AUDIT removes what doesn't. This repo is what came through.

The kitchen is built on the idea that a frontier model in 2026 is very competent at
most things, but its default in any domain is the competent-average version of the
thing. Each skill here is a commitment that drags the model off that median in a
chosen direction. Every one competes with two forces — the unaided frontier model,
which absorbs generic craft with each release, and the owner's time, which every
artifact charges rent on — so deletion is the expected end of every skill here, not
a failure of one.

Each expertise or taste skill earns its place only by beating the unaided current
model on the gap that created it, checked by a runnable probe (`evals/probes.md`),
not assumed. On each model release the probes replay against the bare model; when
every probe passes unaided, the model has absorbed the skill's job and the skill is
deleted. Process skills (changelog, quality-audit) are exempt — their value is the
owner wanting the procedure, which no release absorbs.

─────────────────────

THE SKILLS

- SHADCN-TAILWIND — stack-wide UI discipline for shadcn 4 (Base UI) + Tailwind v4:
  component architecture and token mechanics.
- DESIGN-ENGINEER — always-on design-engineering for shadcn + Tailwind v4 + Next.js
  + Vercel: fluid type/space at the token layer, layout primitives, frequency-aware motion.
- SPEED-DAEMON — optimistic-UI patterns where perceived speed matters (the component
  layer, not a sync engine).
- QUALITY-AUDIT — stack-aware, read-only quality audit for a JS/TS web repo.
- SALTINTESTA — prose tone: articulate ideas in as few good words as possible.
- FLAVORED-MD — GitHub-Flavored Markdown, with the form matched to the content's job.
- ZOOM-OUT — a zoomed-out strategic review of a whole project against its actual purpose.
- CHANGELOG — a skimmable, append-only decision log of what changed and why.

─────────────────────

INSTALL

Served through the `claudia` marketplace (hosted in the agent-kitchen repo):

    /plugin marketplace add claudialnathan/agent-kitchen
    /plugin install skills@claudia

Skills install namespaced — `/skills:design-engineer`, `/skills:saltintesta`, and so on.
The plugin carries no version field (commit-SHA versioning), so a pushed commit reaches
other repos on the next `/plugin marketplace update claudia` → `/plugin update skills@claudia`.

CHANGELOG.md is the provenance ledger: why each skill exists, what it was re-tested
against, and the keep/revise/delete verdicts. The skills themselves carry only a
one-line model pin.
